MADRID , April 10 -LRB- Xinhua -RRB- -- <ENAMEX TYPE="VITAL">Spanish Foreign Minister Carlos Westendorp today protested against smuggling in the British colony of Gibraltar after a Spanish helicopter pursuing suspected smugglers crashed into the sea .</ENAMEX>
Two crewmen from the Civil Guard Corps helicopter were rescued but one remains missing .
The Gibraltar -registered high-speed boat it was chasing was finally seized with three suspects aboard .
<ENAMEX TYPE="VITAL">Westendorp reiterated Spain 's determination to restore sovereignty over the disputed British colony and to combat smuggling in the area </ENAMEX>.
<ENAMEX TYPE="OKAY">Spain has long criticized Britain for inaction to curb smuggling and money laundering in Gibraltar and has tightened controls on its border with the peninsula .</ENAMEX>
The Spanish Foreign Ministry has summoned the British ambassador to Spain to express indignation over the incident , while the Spanish ambassador to Britain has also conveyed Spain 's anger to the British government .
